However, this order would be the one of the first reset, i.e., precisely the one that we don't want. I don't see any other property of the actors persistent among runs and episodes.
Changing the order of the positions would mean to change all the code that relies on that, on benchmark and other client code, where this order is hard-coded.
Since the client-server communication is going to change soon, allowing arbitrary positions and other improvements, it is better not to change this and live with this bug for now.
